<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>SUBZ Platforms Comparison</title>
  <style>
    @import url('https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:wght@400;600;700&family=Space+Grotesk:wght@500;600&display=swap');
    
    body {
      font-family: 'Inter', system-ui, sans-serif;
      background: #0a0a0a;
      color: #e0e0e0;
      margin: 0;
      padding: 40px 20px;
      line-height: 1.5;
    }
    .container {
      max-width: 1100px;
      margin: 0 auto;
      background: #111;
      border-radius: 24px;
      overflow: hidden;
      box-shadow: 0 20px 60px rgba(0,0,0,0.6);
    }
    .header {
      background: linear-gradient(135deg, #1a1a1a, #2a2a2a);
      padding: 40px 50px;
      text-align: center;
      border-bottom: 1px solid #333;
    }
    .title {
      font-family: 'Space Grotesk', sans-serif;
      font-size: 42px;
      font-weight: 600;
      margin: 0 0 8px 0;
      color: #fff;
    }
    .subtitle {
      font-size: 18px;
      color: #aaa;
      margin: 0;
    }
    .main {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: 320px 1fr;
      gap: 0;
    }
    .onlyfans-sidebar {
      background: linear-gradient(180deg, #00d4ff, #0099cc);
      color: #000;
      padding: 50px 40px;
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
    }
    .onlyfans-sidebar h2 {
      font-size: 28px;
      margin: 0 0 30px 0;
      font-weight: 700;
    }
    .stat {
      margin-bottom: 32px;
    }
    .stat-value {
      font-size: 42px;
      font-weight: 700;
      line-height: 1.1;
    }
    .stat-label {
      font-size: 15px;
      opacity: 0.85;
      margin-top: 4px;
    }
    .comparison {
      padding: 50px 40px;
      background: #111;
    }
    table {
      width: 100%;
      border-collapse: collapse;
      margin-top: 20px;
    }
    th, td {
      padding: 16px 12px;
      text-align: left;
      border-bottom: 1px solid #333;
    }
    th {
      background: #1a1a1a;
      font-weight: 600;
      color: #00d4ff;
    }
    .platform-name {
      font-weight: 600;
      font-size: 18px;
    }
    .bar-container {
      height: 24px;
      background: #222;
      border-radius: 12px;
      overflow: hidden;
      margin: 8px 0;
    }
    .bar {
      height: 100%;
      background: linear-gradient(90deg, #00d4ff, #00aaff);
      border-radius: 12px;
    }
    .insight {
      background: #1a1a1a;
      padding: 20px;
      border-radius: 16px;
      margin-top: 30px;
      border-left: 5px solid #00d4ff;
    }
    .footer {
      text-align: center;
      padding: 30px;
      font-size: 14px;
      color: #666;
      background: #0a0a0a;
    }
    .highlight {
      color: #00ffaa;
      font-weight: 600;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <div class="container">
    <div class="header">
      <h1 class="title">SUBZ Platforms Comparison</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">OnlyFans vs. Others • 2024–2026 Data</p>
      <p style="color:#888; margin-top:8px;">Scale, Revenue & Owner Impact in the Creator Subscription Economy</p>
    </div>
    
    <div class="main">
      <!-- OnlyFans Sidebar -->
      <div class="onlyfans-sidebar">
        <h2>OnlyFans</h2>
        <div class="stat">
          <div class="stat-value">$7.2B</div>
          <div class="stat-label">Gross User Spending (2024)</div>
        </div>
        <div class="stat">
          <div class="stat-value">$1.4B</div>
          <div class="stat-label">Platform Revenue</div>
        </div>
        <div class="stat">
          <div class="stat-value">\~$5.8B</div>
          <div class="stat-label">Creator Payouts</div>
        </div>
        <div class="stat">
          <div class="stat-value">\~$1.8B</div>
          <div class="stat-label">Owner Dividends (cumulative)</div>
        </div>
        <div class="stat">
          <div class="stat-value">300M+</div>
          <div class="stat-label">Users</div>
        </div>
        <div class="stat">
          <div class="stat-value">4M+</div>
          <div class="stat-label">Creators</div>
        </div>
        <div class="stat">
          <div class="stat-value">20%</div>
          <div class="stat-label">Platform Fee</div>
        </div>
        <div style="margin-top:auto; font-size:15px; opacity:0.9;">
          <strong>Extreme outlier</strong> in scale & profitability<br>
          • Lean operations (\~45 employees)
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Comparison Table -->
      <div class="comparison">
        <table>
          <thead>
            <tr>
              <th>Platform</th>
              <th>Focus</th>
              <th>Platform Fee</th>
              <th>Key Strength</th>
              <th>Relative Scale</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td class="platform-name">OnlyFans</td>
              <td>Adult-dominant, high-volume</td>
              <td><strong>20%</strong></td>
              <td>Massive paying user base</td>
              <td>
                <div class="bar-container"><div class="bar" style="width:95%"></div></div>
                <span class="highlight">Dominant</span>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="platform-name">Fansly</td>
              <td>Adult, better discovery</td>
              <td>20%</td>
              <td>Built-in recommendations</td>
              <td>
                <div class="bar-container"><div class="bar" style="width:45%"></div></div>
                Strong #2 (Adult)
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="platform-name">Patreon</td>
              <td>Broad: podcasts, art, education</td>
              <td>5–12% + processing</td>
              <td>Community & lower fees</td>
              <td>
                <div class="bar-container"><div class="bar" style="width:35%"></div></div>
                Large but diversified
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="platform-name">Substack</td>
              <td>Newsletters, writing, podcasts</td>
              <td>10% + processing</td>
              <td>Discovery + audience ownership</td>
              <td>
                <div class="bar-container"><div class="bar" style="width:28%"></div></div>
                Strong in writing niches
              </td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>

        <div class="insight">
          <strong>Key Takeaway:</strong> OnlyFans under Leonid Radvinsky generated dramatically higher gross volume and owner returns than any other SUBZ platform across all genres and verticals. Non-adult platforms generally offer lower fees and better tools for sustainable, community-driven growth, but none matched OnlyFans’ raw scale and efficiency.
        </div>

        <div style="margin-top:30px; display:grid; grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr; gap:20px;">
          <div style="background:#1a1a1a; padding:20px; border-radius:16px;">
            <strong>OnlyFans Advantage</strong><br>
            Extreme cash flow efficiency with minimal staff
          </div>
          <div style="background:#1a1a1a; padding:20px; border-radius:16px;">
            <strong>Creator Reality</strong><br>
            Multi-homing is common — many creators use 2–3 platforms depending on content type
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="footer">
      Data from company filings, Sacra, Graphtreon & industry reports (2024–early 2026) • 
      OnlyFans stood out as the most profitable SUBZ platform ever built
    </div>
  </div>
</body>
</html>